# rSwitch - Reconfigurable Switch (Production)

Overview
--------
rSwitch is a production-grade, modular XDP switch implemented using CO-RE BPF
modules. The authoritative implementation resides in `rswitch/`:
- `rswitch/user/` — loader, VOQd user-space, and tools
- `rswitch/bpf/modules/` — per-module BPF programs (CO-RE)
- `rswitch/etc/profiles/` — YAML profiles composing runtime pipelines

Release docs (start here)
- `rswitch/docs/Quick_Start.md` — minimal build & run steps
- `rswitch/docs/How_To_Use.md` — example workflows and tools
- `rswitch/docs/Design_Philosophy.md` — architecture & design rationale
- `rswitch/docs/Module_Developer_Guide.md` — authoring BPF modules, verifier tips
- `rswitch/docs/Scenario_Profiles.md` — example profiles and deployment notes

Build & Run (example)
```bash
# Pre-reqs (Debian/Ubuntu sample):
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y build-essential cmake clang llvm pkg-config make libxdp-dev libbpf-dev linux-headers-$(uname -r)

# Generate CO-RE header and build
make vmlinux
make

# Run a sample profile
PROFILE=etc/profiles/l2.yaml
IFACES=ens34,ens35,ens36
sudo ./build/rswitch_loader --profile "$PROFILE" --ifaces $IFACES
```

Verify (basic)
```bash
sudo bpftool prog list | grep rswitch
sudo bpftool map show | grep rswitch
ps aux | grep rswitch-voqd
```

Developer Notes
- Modules must follow the module ABI (`core/module_abi.h`) and be placed
  in `rswitch/bpf/modules/`.
- Keep BPF verifier friendly: check bounds (`data_end`), use offset masks
  (e.g., `& 0x3F`), avoid unbounded loops and prefer small fixed unrolled
  operations when necessary.
- Rebuild with `make` and use `scripts/hot-reload.sh` or loader hot-reload
  utilities for testing.

Profiles & Deployment
- YAML profiles in `rswitch/etc/profiles/` compose stage order and module
  configuration for production deployments.
- For AF_XDP/VOQd deployments, set NIC queue isolation, IRQ affinity, and
  verify VOQd CPU pinning using `scripts/setup_nic_queues.sh` and
  `rswitch/scripts/rswitch_start.sh`.

Diagnostics & Cleanup
- `rswitch/scripts/rswitch_start.sh` — waits for required maps/VOQd then starts loader.
- `rswitch/scripts/voqd_check.sh` — VOQd readiness & CPU affinity checks.
- `rswitch/scripts/unpin_maps.sh` — helper to unpin maps that persist after loader exit (if present).

Operational Note
- When documentation and scripts differ from the C code, treat `rswitch/`
  C sources as the authoritative implementation for production.

