# rSwitch - Reconfigurable Switch (Production)

rSwitch is a production-ready, modular XDP switch. The authoritative
implementation is under `rswitch/` (loader: `rswitch/user/`, modules: `rswitch/bpf/modules/`).

Release Docs (short links)
- `rswitch/docs/Quick_Start.md` — quick start & build/run examples
- `rswitch/docs/How_To_Use.md` — practical usage & examples
- `rswitch/docs/Design_Philosophy.md` — design rationale
- `rswitch/docs/Module_Developer_Guide.md` — module authoring & verifier notes
- `rswitch/docs/Scenario_Profiles.md` — profiles and deployment notes

Key features
- Modular stage-based BPF pipeline (tail-calls & stages)
- YAML profile driven pipeline composition
- CO-RE BPF modules for portability
- AF_XDP integration + VOQd for scheduling and zero-copy paths

Prerequisites (Debian/Ubuntu example)
```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y build-essential cmake clang llvm pkg-config make libxdp-dev libbpf-dev linux-headers-$(uname -r)
```

Build
```bash
make vmlinux
make
```

Run example
```bash
PROFILE=etc/profiles/l2.yaml
IFACES=ens34,ens35,ens36
sudo ./build/rswitch_loader --profile "$PROFILE" --ifaces $IFACES
```

Verify
```bash
sudo bpftool prog list | grep rswitch
sudo bpftool map show | grep rswitch
ps aux | grep rswitch-voqd
```

Developer notes
- Place modules in `rswitch/bpf/modules/` and follow `core/module_abi.h`.
- Use `make` and `scripts/hot-reload.sh` for iteration and testing.
- Keep BPF verifier in mind: check `data_end`, use offset masks (e.g., `& 0x3F`), unroll or bound loops.

Profiles & deployment tips
- Profiles are under `rswitch/etc/profiles/` and are the canonical runtime composition input.
- For VOQd/AF_XDP: configure NIC queue isolation & CPU affinity using `scripts/setup_nic_queues.sh` and `rswitch/scripts/rswitch_start.sh`.

Diagnostics & cleanup
- `rswitch/scripts/rswitch_start.sh` — waits for maps & VOQd, starts loader
- `rswitch/scripts/voqd_check.sh` — VOQd health & affinity checks
- `rswitch/scripts/unpin_maps.sh` — remove pinned maps on cleanup (if present)

Production note
- Production behavior is defined by the C sources in `rswitch/`. Scripts or PoC artifacts outside `rswitch/` are reference-only.

