# rSwitch - Reconfigurable Switch (Production)

rSwitch is a production-ready, stage-based, modular XDP switch. The
`rswitch/` directory contains authoritative source code, including the
user-space loader (`rswitch/user/`), tools, and BPF modules
(`rswitch/bpf/modules/`). This README is a concise, release-oriented
overview; full guidance is under `rswitch/docs/`.

Release docs (quick links)
- `rswitch/docs/Quick_Start.md` — minimal steps to build/run
- `rswitch/docs/How_To_Use.md` — practical usage & examples
- `rswitch/docs/Design_Philosophy.md` — high-level design
- `rswitch/docs/Module_Developer_Guide.md` — authoring BPF modules and verifier tips
- `rswitch/docs/Scenario_Profiles.md` — common YAML profiles and deployment notes

Key features
- Modular stage-based tail-call pipeline (stages and slots)
- YAML driven profiles to compose the pipeline (`rswitch/etc/profiles/`)
- CO-RE BPF modules (portable across kernels)
- AF_XDP + VOQd for user-space scheduling and zero-copy data paths
- Diagnostic tools and scripts to help boot-time readiness checks and map management

Build prerequisites (Debian/Ubuntu example)
```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt install -y build-essential cmake clang llvm pkg-config make libxdp-dev libbpf-dev linux-headers-$(uname -r)
```

Build & generate CO-RE headers
```bash
make vmlinux
make
```

Run with profile example
```bash
PROFILE=etc/profiles/l2.yaml
IFACES=ens34,ens35,ens36
sudo ./build/rswitch_loader --profile "$PROFILE" --ifaces $IFACES
```

Verify programs & maps
```bash
sudo bpftool prog list | grep rswitch
sudo bpftool map show | grep rswitch
ps aux | grep rswitch-voqd
```

Quick developer notes
- Add BPF module: `rswitch/bpf/modules/my_module.bpf.c` (use `core/module_abi.h`)
- Rebuild: `make` and use `scripts/hot-reload.sh` to update running pipeline
- Follow verifier-friendly patterns: mask offsets (e.g., `& 0x3F`), check `data_end`, unroll small loops

Profiles & deployment
- YAML profiles are in `rswitch/etc/profiles/` and define stage composition and per-module configuration.
- For VOQd / AF_XDP: configure NIC queue isolation, IRQ affinity, and VOQd CPU pinning using `scripts/setup_nic_queues.sh` and `rswitch/scripts/rswitch_start.sh`.

Diagnostics & cleanup
- `rswitch/scripts/rswitch_start.sh` — boot helper that waits for maps & VOQd
- `rswitch/scripts/voqd_check.sh` — VOQd health & affinity check
- `rswitch/scripts/unpin_maps.sh` — (if present) remove pinned components on cleanup

Notes
- Official production behavior and configuration are defined by the C sources
  under `rswitch/`; scripts or YAML in other directories (PoC) are reference only.

